    <h1> Malcolm Reynolds </h1> 
   </div> 
  </div> 
  <div id="content" class="container_12"> 
   <div class="grid_8"> 
    <p> I am a second year <a href="http://engdveiv.ucl.ac.uk/">EngD</a> student at the <a href="http://www.ucl.ac.uk">UCL</a> <a href="http://www.cs.ucl.ac.uk/">Department of Computer Science</a> working under the supervision of <a href="http://www.cs.ucl.ac.uk/staff/G.Brostow/">Gabriel Brostow</a>. I'm interested in applying concepts from Machine Learning, particularly probabilistic methods, to various Computer Vision and Computational Photography problems. </p> 
    <p> I did my undergraduate degree at <a href="http://www.queens.cam.ac.uk">Queens' College Cambridge</a>. My Director of Studies was Robin Walker and my final year project was supervised by <a href="http://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/~sbh11/">Sean Holden</a>. After graduating I joined UCL on the MSc Intelligent Systems course (now <a href="http://www-typo3.cs.ucl.ac.uk/admissions/msc_ml/">MSc Machine Learning</a>). My thesis was supervised by <a href="http://www.cs.ucl.ac.uk/staff/m.herbster/">Mark Herbster</a>. </p> 
    <p> I organise the weekly Computer Vision Reading Group, where we take turns to present a paper or discuss a topic. All are welcome, please see <a href="cvrg.html">this page</a> for details. </p> 
    <p> Thanks to <a href="http://www.cs.ucl.ac.uk/staff/Y.Doron/">Yotam</a> for letting me steal his webpage formatting. </p> 
